<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="372" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,295,538]" pageId="15" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,403,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="372">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityName="Park &amp; Karisch" authorityYear="2022" box="[671,1017,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Dragmatucha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediolinea" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[671,830,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="372">D. mediolinea</emphasis>
Park &amp; Karisch
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1029,1119,403,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="372">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1029,1119,403,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="372" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but can be distinguished by the forewing less elongated, ground color more grayish brown, antemedian band weakly developed. The female genitalia can be easily distinguished by the abdominal sternite VIII uniquely modified with heavily sclerotized median plate elongated distally and lateral lobes triangularly produced with sharply pointed apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810532" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810532" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810532/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="372" startId="15.[151,250,1978,2002]" targetBox="[161,1431,582,1936]" targetPageId="15">
