<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,360,762,788]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[366,501,763,789]" name="Ivory Coast" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Ivory Coast</collectingCountry>
, Montagne District.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="373" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, - 
<emphasis box="[840,924,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="373">ovarius</emphasis>
(= ovary), referring to the egg-shaped signum in the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
